WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:02.684
Long tasks create a second problem.

2
00:00:02.145 --> 00:00:10.239
Even well-curated context eventually fills as the Agent takes actions, observes results, fixes errors, and accumulates decisions.

3
00:00:09.723 --> 00:00:13.976
A task that lasts hours may exceed the usable window several times.

4
00:00:13.495 --> 00:00:15.685
Compaction is the first lever.

5
00:00:15.129 --> 00:00:25.559
Summarize the conversation or trace, start a fresh window, and carry forward the decisions, unresolved bugs, constraints, evidence, and next actions needed for continuity.

6
00:00:24.982 --> 00:00:29.278
Raw tool output that has already served its purpose can usually disappear.

7
00:00:28.794 --> 00:00:34.147
Compaction has a risk: a subtle detail that looks unimportant now may become critical later.

8
00:00:33.592 --> 00:00:38.147
Anthropic recommends tuning for high recall first, then improving precision.

9
00:00:37.603 --> 00:00:42.562
Losing a decisive constraint is more expensive than carrying a little extra context.

10
00:00:42.076 --> 00:00:44.622
Structured notes provide another layer.

11
00:00:44.051 --> 00:00:51.866
The Agent writes progress, milestones, discoveries, and open questions outside the window, then reloads the relevant note later.

12
00:00:51.300 --> 00:00:55.836
This makes working state durable without keeping the entire conversation active.

13
00:00:55.373 --> 00:00:58.803
Specialized agents can isolate deep exploration.

14
00:00:58.257 --> 00:01:05.889
A lead Agent keeps the high-level plan while focused agents investigate separate questions with clean contexts and return condensed findings.

15
00:01:05.347 --> 00:01:09.758
This pays off when parallel research value exceeds coordination cost.

16
00:01:09.286 --> 00:01:11.111
Choose by task shape.

17
00:01:10.596 --> 00:01:19.401
Use compaction for conversational continuity, notes for iterative work with clear milestones, and specialized agents for independent deep investigations.

18
00:01:18.865 --> 00:01:25.978
Whichever method you choose, the handoff must preserve outcome, decisions, evidence, unknowns, and next action.

19
00:01:25.467 --> 00:01:29.993
First, compact long traces into high-recall continuity summaries.

20
00:01:29.532 --> 00:01:33.664
Second, keep durable working state in structured external notes.

21
00:01:33.201 --> 00:01:38.391
Third, use specialized agents only when focused exploration justifies coordination.
